title: Analysis: Big moments for women at the men's World Cup
description: An unexpected result of the US Men's National Team reaching the knockout round of 16 at the FIFA World Cup in Qatar is that the US Women's National Team will get its largest collective payday, equally splitting $13 million in winnings with the men.

title: Landslide leaves at least two dead and dozens missing in Brazil
description: A landslide in the southern Brazilian state of Paraná killed at least two people and left dozens missing on Wednesday, according to officials.

title: Qatar World Cup chief says between 400 and 500 migrant workers have died in projects connected to the tournament
description: World Cup chief Hassan Al-Thawadi said that between 400 and 500 migrant workers have died as a result of work done on projects connected to the tournament -- a greater figure than Qatari officials have cited previously.

title: Argentina progresses to World Cup knockout stages with win
description: Lionel Messi had a penalty saved but Argentina booked its ticket to the knockout phase of the 2022 World Cup with a 2-0 victory over Poland.

title: Inflation in Europe drops for the first time in 17 months
description: For the first time in 17 months, inflation in Europe is easing.

title: China to punish internet users for 'liking' posts in crackdown after zero-Covid protests
description: Internet users in China will soon be held liable for liking posts deemed illegal or harmful, sparking fears that the world's second largest economy plans to control social media like never before.

title: China's Zhengzhou, home to world's largest iPhone factory, ends Covid lockdown
description: The central Chinese city of Zhengzhou, home to the world's largest iPhone factory, has lifted a five-day Covid lockdown, in a move that analysts have called a much-needed relief for Apple and its main supplier Foxconn.

title: Deep cuts at AMC Networks signals turbulent time for media industry
description: "The mechanisms for the monetization of content are in disarray."

title: US calls for the release of Cambodian labor activist
description: The United States on Tuesday said it was deeply concerned by Cambodia's arrest of union leader Chhim Sithar and called for her release and that of other detained trade unionists.
